******
[1] Minnesota
Date: 12 Aug 2019
Source: CBS Local Minnesota [edited]
https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2019/08/12/3-rare-horse-diseases-found-in-minnesota/


Three rare horse diseases were recently found in Otter Tail, Pine and Swift counties, according to the Minnesota Board of Animal Health. Recent testing shows equine infectious anemia (EIA) was found in Pine County.

Equine infectious anemia requires infected horses to be euthanized or quarantined for life due to lack of treatment or vaccine. It is not known to affect humans.

"This is also a high-risk time of year for horses to become infected with these diseases," said Dr. Courtney Wheeler, Board of Animal Health equine program director. The infected horse was euthanized.

For more information on the cases, visit the Minnesota Board of Animal Health.

