[So many articles tell us about horses dying of EIA. What I do not see is anyone willing to do or doing research on creating a vaccine for this disease. The technology and know-how are surely out there, yet no research papers or progress reports.

It is in all probability a funding issue. For as we hear about a lot of horses dying from this disease, USDA estimates that it is only 1-2 percent of the USA's equine population. Nevertheless, that is a lot of horses and a lot of heartache, and it remains a very sad situation. - Mod.TG

